15.body: Smart contract language with formal verification and the idea of ownership baked into its programming model. The stdlib for the 0L network is written in move. The stdlib defines some of the core protocol of the network, and is able to be upgrade on the running network with a 2/3rd validator vote. The stdlib defines basic protocol rules: consensus, account creation, tx validation, etc. see move_stdlib.md

7.body: In this chapter and throughout the book, we’ll show some commands used in the terminal. Lines that you should enter in a terminal all start with $. You don’t need to type in the $ character; it indicates the start of each command. Lines that don’t start with $ typically show the output of the previous command. Additionally, PowerShell-specific examples will use > rather than $.
7.title: Command Line Notation
